<LegalLayout title="Cookie Policy" description="How Agent Junky uses cookies, and how to control them.">
  <p><em>Last updated: 22 July 2026</em></p>

  <p>
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They're used to
    remember preferences, measure traffic, and serve relevant ads.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies we use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> — used to remember your cookie consent choice. Without these, we'd ask again on every page.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies</strong> — set by Google AdSense to serve and personalize ads, and to measure ad performance.</li>
    <li><strong>Affiliate tracking cookies</strong> — set by third-party retailers/affiliate networks when you click an affiliate link, to attribute any resulting purchase.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your consent</h2>
  <p>
    On your first visit, a banner asks you to accept or decline non-essential cookies (advertising).
    You can change your mind at any time by clearing your browser's cookies for this site, which will
    show the banner again.
  </p>

  <h2>Controlling cookies elsewhere</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Manage Google's personalized ads at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a></li>
    <li>Opt out of interest-based advertising broadly via <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Your Online Choices</a> (EU/UK)</li>
    <li>Block or delete cookies in your browser's own privacy settings</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:info@agentjunky.com">info@agentjunky.com</a></p>
</LegalLayout>
